<br>
When I pulled fear a while ago I didnt have the right resist gear and died multiple times.  (10+)I was able to get rev, but many times just a regular res.  After losing ep, that takes me farther from my goal; to say nothing of the time during the raid. Why should my efforts go to a non-federation member?  It was cool that we got an epic piece and some peeps got armor.<br>
<br>
If a nice person wants to attend, thats great! But why in the hell should they be allowed to get loot from it?<br>
<br>
To the person that said peeps can come over to your house.  Sure they can come, but they dont also take stuff.<br>
<br>
If someone wants to raid a plane or a zone then they are welcome.  If they want to get loot then they should be a part of the group.  When your grouped up in sebillis do you offer to let others in the zone roll on the loot? No, the people in the group rolls.  I can see if we ask a certain person to help out, but hell there are 12 guilds in the federation.  If we cant flesh out a planned raid with 12 guilds we have issues.<br>
<br>
Why are people bringing up trashing uber?  Most of the times there is an inferiority complex that causes them to go on the attack.  Trying to work towards goals and getting loot does not mean that you have to abandon having fun and being nice.  If you want to do different zones you need to have good equipment in order to do it. Period, you can whine about skill and techniques but you need ac/resist/damage output.<br>
<br>
As far as Unhomed and Vigdis asking us not to attend events.<br>
<br>
Dindawen left out that every member is a admin/moderator on the message board and we only have 1 rule. Period...nothing else. How is that political?  But I can tell you I will not attend these raids as I trust Vigdis 100%, and I know, without asking, that noone else in Unhomed will attend these raids either.  Why? I know the peeps of Unhomed.<br>
