<br>
<br>
Maybe I'm thickheaded, but it's *my* understanding that it's up to the raid leader whether non-Fed people can come along. Has this changed? Has it become an official Fed policy that you *must* be in one of their guilds to attend a raid posted on the Fed board?<br>
<br>
As far as I see it, Vidgis (and Unhomed) are saying &quot;You must be in the Federation to get our help&quot; .. so I read that as &quot;If there's non-Fed people on the raid, we won't be. Choose between us and them. We didn't join the Federation to help people outside of it.&quot;<br>
<br>
While Bendi seems to be saying &quot;Hey, it's just a game, I'll help anyone who's willing to help me. No one gets a free ride on a raid, everyone contributes something, and as long as they're friendly, nice, people, I'll help them while they help me.&quot;<br>
<br>
I'm not judging one way or the other, and feel free to correct me if I'm getting your message wrong, it just seems that this one issue is getting bandied about and causing a lot of problems and hard feelings. I think one of the Federation admins really needs to step in and say &quot;Guys, it's up to the individual raid leaders to decide. Run your raids the way you want them to be run, and if the raid leader doesn't run it the way you want it to be run, don't sign up.&quot; Or &quot;This is the Federation offical policy on outsider attendance..&quot; or even &quot;Hold the keyboard a sec.. We're debating and discussing the matter, we'll get a decision down to you soon. We promise.&quot; .. Right now it's getting batted around so much because there is no input from the higher ups. (Again, as I see it. I, of course, being an outsider, can't see what's going on behind the closed doors.)<br>
